18/01/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The Romanian-US consultations on the establishment of American bases in Europe are expected to resume soon at technical level, according to the Romanian Defence Ministry's state secretary George Cristian Maior. 
In a statement for Rompres news agency last Friday (16 January), Maior said that these talks would determine the locations in European countries and facilities that could be used by the American troops. 
Commenting on the possibility of relocating and placing US bases on Romanian territory, he said that no final decision had been made yet. 
(Rompres - 17/01/04)
